Text:
Guys learn once when downloading pirated software that includes keygen or patches, its detected by Anti-Virus! its false/positive ignore it.

-Stun

Common sense detection about this false positive:
1) VIP uploader (green skull)
2) This isn't their only upload
3) Huge history of other uploads
4) Has files being used by 10000+ people
5) "NOD32	5327	2010.07.30 -"
6) "Kaspersky 5.5.10 2010.07.31 2010-07-31 0.42 -"
7) "Trojan.Win32.Generic"
8) Detection limited to scanners with known high false positive rate or poor quality
9) Being paranoid isn't a license for stupidity

Anyway, thanks Stun.
